  <p class="big">Research and Inspiration</p>
  <p>
    The visual style drew heavily from neon-drenched arcade carpets, geometric
    patterns, and the vibrant color palettes of the late 90s and early 2000s. I
    pulled references from CRT-era gaming consoles, my own elementary school
    yearbook spreads, and the chaotic maximalism of childhood arcade visits,
    creating a look that felt stylishly retro.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="side-by-side">
  <p class="big">Building The World</p>
  <p>
    I began by blocking out the scene with simple primitives, structuring the
    layout around four custom-modeled arcade machines that served as
    centerpieces for key BoomTV milestones. From the start, I aimed to make the
    environment feel alive, with dynamic lighting, animated UI, and immersive
    camera moves that echoed the playful, high-energy feel of classic arcade
    spaces.
  </p>
</div>

