<div class="side-by-side">
  <p class="big">Exploring Stylized 3D with Grease Pencil</p>
  <p>
    Having primarily worked with realistic 3D animation, I saw this project as
    an opportunity to experiment with stylized illustration within a 3D space.
    The ability to hand-draw directly onto 3D planes with Blender's Grease
    Pencil introduced to me an entirely new layer of creative expression! After
    an initial learning curve, it became a natural part of my workflow.
  </p>
</div>
<div class="side-by-side">
  <p class="big">Workflow Evolutions</p>
  <p>
    When I began this project, my drawing tool was an iPad and Apple Pencil via
    Astropad, allowing me to sketch directly in Blender. While the limited
    screen space presented challenges, drawing in Grease Pencil was so rewarding
    that it led me to upgrade my setup. Design is a constant process of
    exploration and iteration, which is the mindset I bring into every creative
    challenge.
  </p>
</div>

